DBVisualizer - https://www.dbvis.com
Open Source Free version and DBVisalizerPro is a commercial edition
As a universal database management tool, DBVisualizer does not have its own data model. 
Instead, it supports the data models of the various databases it can connect to. 
This includes relational databases like MySQL, PostgreSQL, and Oracle; NoSQL databases like MongoDB; and in-memory databases like H2 and SQLite.
DBVisualizer is a desktop application that runs on your local machine. 
It connects to local or remote databases and helps you manage tables, views, stored procedures, and perform various database operations
Since DBVisualizer is a GUI tool, Java and Python do not access it directly.
However, you can use Java and Python to interact with the various databases that DBVisualizer supports.
